{Speech 17 Answer 21}{}{Ah, I see. Well anyway, he's actually MY servant, he just got into trouble while I had business in another city.}
{Speech 18}{}{Worried? What's there to worry about. We're not animals.  He's not beaten, not cut. He's fed regularly, he washes every day. Do you think he's badly off here?}
{Speech 18 Answer 22}{}{Of course she's worried. They're not animals either, as you put it. They have a son, they love each other. Separation is hard for those who love.}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Really?  Then there's truly nothing to worry about. I'll be going.}
{Speech 19}{}{Of course, citizen. That's what we're here for. Please sign the register. Where should I send him?}
{Speech 19 Answer 20}{}{The tent in the outer courtyard, near the Guard barracks. He'll find it easily.}
{Speech 20}{}{Understood. Right now he's in quarantine, under observation, like all the newcomers. As soon as the quarantine ends, he'll be sent to the indicated address.}
